com.delphix.masking.api.provider

Interface CryptoService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CryptoServiceImpl

    public interface CryptoService
    This interface provides access to keys and other key-based cryptographic operations. Objects implementing this interface act as lightweight wrappers around a single key. More keys may be generated deterministically using the derive methods provided.

        static final int MINIMUM_KEY_SIZE_BYTES

      • shuffleListNoCollisions

        void shuffleListNoCollisions(@Nonnull
                             java.util.List<?> list)
        Shuffle the provided list in-place. The resulting permutation depends on this provider's key. For lists with at least two items, the resulting permutation is guaranteed to move each item to a new position.
        Parameters:
        list - The list to shuffle.
